LLC_BI__Loan__c

LLC_BI__Current_LTV__c
Current LTV
Formula (Percent)
true
false
This field is automatically populated via a formula. It stores the current LTV of the loan based on its Collateral Mgmt records. If the Product Feature is NOT a Line of Credit, or if the Product Feature does not exist, this is the formula: (Principal Balance + Total Prior Lien Amount from all Collateral)/ Collateral Value from all Collateral. If the Product Feature is a Line of Credit, this is the formula: Original Loan Amount / (Collateral Value from all Collateral - Total Prior Lien Amount from all Collateral)

LLC_BI__Line_Of_Credit__c
Line Of Credit
Checkbox
false
false
This field is manually selected. When enabled, this product feature specifies that a product is a line of credit. This flag is used to override the relationship stats criteria "UsePrincipalBalance=true", so that a line of credit product always uses "Original Amount" for exposure calculations. Additionally, the LLC_BI__Current_LTV__c on Loan uses Original Amount for its calculation. When disabled, the relationship stats criteria is not overwritten, and an exposure calculation with "UsePrincipalBalance=true" criteria will use the principal balance. Similarly, LLC_BI__Current_LTV__c will use principal balance for its calculation. By default, this is disabled.

When it does match, depending on what fields are populated on the product state config record, the loan may be updated in the system or customer portal and/or reports may be updated.
